/target
# Cargo.lock IS committed: neotop is a binary crate, so locking
# the exact dependency set is what guarantees reproducible CI
# builds (`cargo --locked`) and bisects. The Cargo book recommends
# tracking it for binaries and excluding it only for libraries.
.DS_Store
*.swp
*.swo
.idea/
.vscode/

# Obsidian vault — per-user UI state + local caches. Plugin binaries
# are tracked so a fresh clone gets the same toolset as neosandbox
# without waiting for Obsidian's community-plugin downloader.
.obsidian/workspace.json
.obsidian/workspace-mobile.json
.obsidian/cache
.devin/
